"Cordell G.A., Colvard M.D.","Natural products in a world out-of-balance",2007,"Arkivoc","2007","7",,"97","115",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33846171178&partnerID=40&md5=09dd23e8b114000b17e87045bbc9b002","University of Illinois at Chicago, Chicago, IL 60612, United States","Cordell, G.A., University of Illinois at Chicago, Chicago, IL 60612, United States; Colvard, M.D., University of Illinois at Chicago, Chicago, IL 60612, United States","The natural world is careening out of balance in many different ways. Uncontrolled population growth, global warming, loss of biodiversity, and emerging new diseases, has fostered increasing drug resistance, dependence on synthetic chemicals and drugs, unregulated natural medicines, abused natural products, and the use of natural products as agents of mass intimidation, incapacitation, and death. This is not a sustainable situation for the planet. Plants are the basis of the ecological homeostasis of Earth and its' living organisms, including the human species, and plant-based medicinal agents are used world-wide by humans and animals to treat a myriad of ailments. But, how will quality human health care, particularly in the form of locally sustainable medicinal agents, be delivered to a burgeoning global population? ©ARKAT.","Natural products; Public health; Standardization; Traditional medicine",,,,,,,"Cordell, G.A., Colvard, M.D., (2005) J. Ethnopharmacol, 100, pp. 5-14; Colvard, M.D., Cordell, G.A., Villalobos, R., Sanchos, G., Soejarto, D.D., Pestle, W., Lobo Echeverri, T., Michel, M., (2006) J. Ethnopharmacol, , In press; Cordell, G.A., (2005) Proceedings of the 2nd International Conference and Exposition on the Modernization of Traditional Chinese Medicine, pp. 405-418. , Chengdu, People's Republic of China; Cordell, G.A., (1995) Phytochemistry, 40, pp. 1585-1612; Cordell, G.A., (2000) Phytochemistry, 55, pp. 463-480; Cordell, G.A., (2002) Rev. Quim, 16, pp. 5-12; Cordell, G.A., (2002) Phytochem. R